WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:01.428
Previously on <i>Riverdale...</i>

00:02.659 --> 00:04.385
That kid is a star.

00:04.454 --> 00:06.053
- Can I kiss you?
- Archie.

00:07.891 --> 00:09.857
You broke the code.
Turn in your jackets and go.

00:09.926 --> 00:12.026
I'm a Serpent by blood.

00:12.095 --> 00:15.263
- What's this?
- A gang, and you're the leader.

00:15.331 --> 00:18.132
<i>I think my mom may have
hired someone to shoot my father</i>

00:18.201 --> 00:21.502
so that she could make a profit
from the sale of his drug operation.

00:21.571 --> 00:23.404
Let's end this nightmare.

00:23.473 --> 00:26.407
<i>Find the drugs and destroy them
before my mom sells everything.</i>

00:26.476 --> 00:29.911
What the hell did you do? I used the cash
from the sale to pay off Governor Dooley.

00:29.979 --> 00:33.281
<i>And now my buyer is coming,
and they are gonna want blood.</i>

00:33.349 --> 00:35.249
Here's your money.
Or as much as we could get of it.

00:35.318 --> 00:37.985
We'll figure out
a payment plan for the rest.

00:41.891 --> 00:43.991
<i>Gryphons and Gargoyles.</i>

00:44.060 --> 00:46.828
<i>Serpents and Ghoulies.</i>

00:46.896 --> 00:50.198
<i>Riverdale was a veritable jungle
of mythological creatures,</i>

00:50.266 --> 00:53.267
<i>species jockeying for power,</i>

00:53.336 --> 00:55.036
<i>and the dark heart of it all...</i>

00:55.104 --> 00:57.338
Good morning, sunshine.

00:57.407 --> 00:58.806
Wakey, wakey.

00:59.843 --> 01:01.309
Breakfast is served.

01:01.377 --> 01:03.144
Wow, Mom.

01:04.947 --> 01:07.114
That's way better
than my normal breakfast.

01:08.384 --> 01:10.418
- Morning.
- Morning.

01:10.487 --> 01:13.754
- Did you sleep on it wrong?
- There's no right way to sleep on a couch.

01:13.823 --> 01:15.189
- Do you want the bed?
- No, I'm fine.

01:15.258 --> 01:18.259
I need coffee.

01:18.328 --> 01:21.295
You let her drink coffee?

01:21.364 --> 01:25.299
Okay, it's fine by me.
Help yourself.

01:25.368 --> 01:27.235
I gotta get to work.

01:27.303 --> 01:29.170
Hey, if you need anything,
you call me.

01:35.011 --> 01:36.677
- Morning, Betty.
- Morning, Mom.

01:39.449 --> 01:41.749
Is that your wedding dress?

01:41.818 --> 01:44.519
It is. I'm getting it altered.

01:47.123 --> 01:49.423
Why, are you getting married?

01:49.492 --> 01:52.527
In a sense. I'm being baptized
into the Farm.

01:54.898 --> 01:57.365
Sorry, you're what?

01:57.433 --> 01:59.267
Edgar says I'm finally ready.

01:59.335 --> 02:03.204
All of the women from the Farm are
gathering Sunday night at the new facility.

02:09.913 --> 02:12.914
<i>Mija?</i>
Can I see you for a moment?

02:17.687 --> 02:19.887
I've been getting caught up on things.

02:21.558 --> 02:24.959
Hopefully, you can answer a
question that's been nagging me.

02:25.028 --> 02:26.761
In the short time I was laid up,

02:26.829 --> 02:31.999
some very valuable equipment and
stock went missing from my prison.

02:32.068 --> 02:36.070
Didn't Mom say that she had to have
it destroyed because of the Feds?

02:38.074 --> 02:39.173
Yeah, she did.

02:41.578 --> 02:45.112
Tall Boy, an ex-Serpent,
tried to kill me.

02:46.249 --> 02:48.249
FP, an ex-Serpent,
is now sheriff.

02:48.318 --> 02:51.652
Gladys, a Toledo Serpent,
is back in town after years away,

02:51.721 --> 02:55.723
and suddenly, I'm out
some very valuable assets.

02:55.792 --> 02:59.026
If I didn't know better, I'd say
the Joneses pulled a fast one on me.

02:59.095 --> 03:03.664
They strike me as opportunists,
not master schemers.

03:03.733 --> 03:06.567
At a minimum, they would certainly
need the help of someone close to me

03:06.636 --> 03:07.868
to pull anything like this off.

03:10.239 --> 03:13.374
Oh, well.
The truth will shake out.

03:15.812 --> 03:17.778
It always does.

03:21.884 --> 03:25.453
How about we skip class,
catch a matinee at the Bijou?

03:25.521 --> 03:28.489
Oh, wow, you're sweeter than
a strawberry milkshake, Arch.

03:28.558 --> 03:30.891
But I've got a meeting
with our college advisor.

03:32.428 --> 03:34.128
Maybe we can meet up after school?

03:34.197 --> 03:37.064
- Actually, I'm training with Mr. Keller then.
- Oh.

03:37.133 --> 03:39.667
Are there any college
scholarships for boxing out there?

03:39.736 --> 03:43.137
No. But stepping in
between those ropes, Josie,

03:43.206 --> 03:46.073
it gets me and keeps me in a
good headspace. Helps me focus.

03:47.744 --> 03:49.777
I forget about everything else
outside the ring.

03:52.515 --> 03:55.216
Well, almost everything else.

03:55.284 --> 03:59.053
Yeah, well, just don't go messing
up that pretty face, Andrews.

03:59.122 --> 04:00.688
It's growing on me.

04:01.991 --> 04:03.791
It was the weirdest thing, Jug.

04:03.860 --> 04:05.926
My mom's usually rubbing
the Farm in my face,

04:05.995 --> 04:10.865
but now she's shutting me out.
Like she's washed her hands of me.

04:10.933 --> 04:12.366
Which is even more terrifying.

04:12.435 --> 04:15.269
They're definitely up to
some serious shadiness,

04:15.338 --> 04:17.838
like they're entrenching.

04:17.906 --> 04:19.807
I was trying to dig up
some dirt online on the Farm,

04:19.875 --> 04:24.211
and I couldn't even find a photograph
of Edgar Evernever. Not one, Jug.

04:24.280 --> 04:25.880
That's weird.

04:25.948 --> 04:27.982
If you really want to protect your
mother, maybe it's worthwhile

04:28.051 --> 04:30.885
just embracing
this whole baptism thing.

04:30.953 --> 04:32.687
Or at least pretending to embrace it.

04:32.755 --> 04:35.222
It may help you keep tabs
on her. Make sure she's safe.

04:37.226 --> 04:38.392
Come on.

04:42.665 --> 04:43.931
Where the hell is everyone else?

04:44.000 --> 04:45.366
Oh, we're down another eight.

04:45.435 --> 04:47.802
- Another eight?
- All girls.

04:47.870 --> 04:49.103
Where are they all going?

04:49.172 --> 04:51.105
Turns out Toni and Cheryl
started their own gang.

04:51.174 --> 04:54.208
- All the girls are defecting to it.
- The Pretty Poisons.

04:56.212 --> 04:58.345
So, what do you want
us to do, boss?

04:58.414 --> 05:02.149
Nothing. This is all because
I banished Cheryl and Toni.

05:03.319 --> 05:04.852
I just need to talk to Toni,

05:04.921 --> 05:06.854
get her back into the Serpent fold,
and the rest will come back, too.

05:06.923 --> 05:08.989
They need to be reminded
what it means to be a Serpent.

05:10.827 --> 05:12.093
I'll make this right.

05:13.696 --> 05:14.995
One, one, two.

05:16.833 --> 05:17.832
Spider.

05:20.837 --> 05:22.670
Keep your hand up, right?

05:22.739 --> 05:24.538
It's the first thing I learned
boxing in the army.

05:24.607 --> 05:27.174
And you've got a nasty habit
of telegraphing your punches.

05:27.243 --> 05:29.443
You do that with an experienced
fighter in the ring,

05:29.512 --> 05:31.779
and he'll see you
coming from a mile away.

05:31.848 --> 05:33.881
All due respect, Mr. Keller,

05:33.950 --> 05:35.616
those guys at L&L
sure as hell didn't.

05:37.487 --> 05:39.720
Get me a fight, a real fight,

05:39.789 --> 05:41.689
with some of these guys training in
here, I can show you.

05:41.758 --> 05:46.293
Archie, you've got good speed,
all right, and you've got some power,

05:47.296 --> 05:49.230
but you've got no technique.

05:49.298 --> 05:52.733
You have to learn that, and until you do,
don't even think about your first fight.

05:53.669 --> 05:55.302
How long are we talking about?

05:55.371 --> 05:58.405
Archie, you're not ready.

05:58.474 --> 06:01.108
How are we meant to know that
until you get me in the ring?

06:01.177 --> 06:03.711
I need to know if boxing is
gonna be a viable option for me.

06:04.580 --> 06:06.247
Trust me.

06:06.315 --> 06:08.315
Boxing is not something
you want to do half-assed.

06:10.386 --> 06:11.886
Good workout.
Hit the showers.

06:17.860 --> 06:18.859
This week's payment.

06:22.832 --> 06:24.398
So, here's the deal.

06:24.467 --> 06:28.169
My dad suspects that you and FP
are behind his recent troubles,

06:28.237 --> 06:31.338
that you came back to Riverdale
to steal his drug trade.

06:32.408 --> 06:34.441
Why is that my problem?

06:34.510 --> 06:38.779
Because he's fired up about rebuilding his
empire, and you don't want to get in his way.

06:38.848 --> 06:41.649
Also, maybe you don't want
him to find out

06:41.717 --> 06:45.619
that Mommy tried to sell his business
out from under him, am I right?

06:46.589 --> 06:48.656
No comment.

06:48.724 --> 06:52.960
Clue me in on your dad's moves and that
debt you owe me, I might ease it slightly.

06:54.330 --> 06:56.931
You want me to spy on my father?
For you?

06:58.234 --> 06:59.967
That's not gonna happen.

07:00.036 --> 07:03.637
I don't want to cause a drama here.
I just want to get what's owed to me,

07:04.574 --> 07:06.407
plus a little bit more.

07:06.475 --> 07:11.011
And now it looks as though I'm in a race
with your dad to rebuild the candy trade.

07:11.080 --> 07:15.416
Who do you want to be
in charge, me or him?

07:16.152 --> 07:17.084
You.

07:19.722 --> 07:21.322
I want my family out of drugs.

07:21.390 --> 07:23.624
So, we both want the same thing.
What's the problem?

07:24.660 --> 07:27.361
Either you get Hiram
out of my way,

07:27.430 --> 07:30.531
or sniff out what he's doing.

07:30.600 --> 07:32.800
Let me know, so I can
stay ahead of him.

07:35.504 --> 07:37.504
I know what you're after, Elio,

07:37.573 --> 07:39.273
but it ain't happening here.

07:39.342 --> 07:41.942
Any boxer in this dump
would be lucky to fight Randy.

07:42.011 --> 07:44.645
- It's just good business.
- For you, sure. Not for me.

07:49.185 --> 07:50.117
Elio.

07:51.220 --> 07:53.387
Archie Andrews?
You training here?

07:53.456 --> 07:55.890
Yeah.

07:55.958 --> 07:59.927
And if you need an opponent for your
guy, I'll do it. I'll take the fight.

07:59.996 --> 08:01.362
How many bouts
you have under your belt?

08:01.964 --> 08:03.297
Well, none.

08:03.366 --> 08:05.332
But I gotta get in the ring.
Otherwise, what's the point?

08:07.103 --> 08:10.704
Well, it's your lucky day.
Congrats! He's got your first fight.

08:10.773 --> 08:13.340
One condition, I need you to
guarantee me that you'll lose.

08:15.411 --> 08:17.278
Are you serious?

08:17.346 --> 08:19.947
Throw the fight,
make Randy here look good doing it.

08:23.019 --> 08:25.252
No, Elio.
I'm not taking a dive.

08:25.321 --> 08:27.021
I'm offering you
a golden opportunity

08:27.089 --> 08:29.256
to start to make a name for
yourself. This is how it goes.

08:29.325 --> 08:32.493
Start building a rep.
First step to becoming a champ

08:32.561 --> 08:34.061
is fighting a champ.

08:34.130 --> 08:36.697
Boxing's like any other profession.
You've gotta pay your dues.

08:36.765 --> 08:37.831
But, in this case,

08:37.900 --> 08:40.534
you also get paid.
Five thousand dollars.

08:41.837 --> 08:44.338
- For one fight?
- Three rounds, that's all.

08:44.407 --> 08:47.007
My guy gets another win,
you get on the board.

08:47.076 --> 08:49.910
I mean, for a guy like you,
this is as good as it's gonna get.

08:51.714 --> 08:52.913
I want to get paid first.

08:53.883 --> 08:54.949
Today, now.

08:55.017 --> 08:57.217
Half now, half after the fight.

09:00.289 --> 09:03.223
You're gonna thank me, Red.
Let's go.

